Sentencas: The corrugated solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) can effectively improve energy density and transformation efficiency compared with conventional planar SOFC, but its stability and durability have not been systematically analyzed.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: The residual stress of SOFC may lead to crack initiation and propagation during cooling process, so stress distributions of planar and corrugated SOFCs are simulated to analyze the location of crack initiation.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: The materials of electrolyte, anode, and cathode in this paper are yttria-stabilization zirconia (YSZ), Ni-YSZ, and strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM), respectively.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: The result shows that the edge of cell is more prone to cracking.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: Therefore, precracks including edge crack and middle crack are introduced into anode-electrolyte interfaces to investigate crack propagation of two types of SOFCs during cooling process.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: For corrugated SOFC, the cracks propagate more slowly, and the cell is less prone to interfacial delamination compared with planar SOFC.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: In addition, the interface energy release rates are obtained to further analyze crack propagation of two types of SOFCs, and the corrugated SOFC has lower energy release rate.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process

Sentencas: The research in this paper provides guidance for stability analysis and lays a foundation for future mechanical analysis of corrugated SOFC.
Titulo: Crack propagation of planar and corrugated solid oxide fuel cells during cooling process
